name: polypeptide N-acetylgalactosaminyltransferase
comment: Requires both Mn2+ and Ca2+. The glycosyl residue is transferred to threonine or serine hydroxy groups on the polypeptide core of submaxillary mucin, kappa-casein, apofetuin and some other acceptors of high molecular mass.

references.title: Purification and characterization of UDP-GalNAc:polypeptide N-acetylgalactosamine transferase from an ascites hepatoma, AH 66.
Purification and characterization of UDP-N-acetylgalactosamine-kappa-casein polypeptide N-acetylgalactosaminyltransferase from mammary-gland of lactating cow.
